      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1) operates under institutional SQA plan with documented version control, regression testing, and change management procedures.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R1 used under FDA CDRH institutional SQA plan. Version-controlled input decks, automated regression suite executed prior to each study run, and change-control log maintained. Achieved level meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver correctness demonstrated via benchmark problems with known analytical solutions for beam bending and contact mechanics.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical verified against NAFEMS benchmark suite and internal cantilever-beam analytical solutions. Contact formulation validated against Hertzian contact reference. No code defects identified relevant to this analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates < 2% change in QoIs between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on representative screw-rod assembly. QoI change between medium and fine mesh: 1.3% (stiffness), 1.7% (yield force). GCI = 3.8%. Discretization error bounded and within acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver (SPARSE) employed; iterative residuals not applicable. Energy balance monitored across all load increments; maximum imbalance 0.04%. Exceeds required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments against documented simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review conducted by second analyst at DePuy Synthes. Boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and loading protocol verified against pre-approved simulation plan. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) and contact formulation (augmented Lagrangian, frictional) demonstrated appropriate for quasi-static metallic implant compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.2 GPa) calibrated from coupon tests of Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM E8. Augmented Lagrangian frictional contact (μ=0.2, cobalt-chrome rod on titanium screw saddle) consistent with literature. Model form judged adequate for quasi-static loading regime."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions sourced from traceable measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "Material properties measured from production-lot coupons (n=5 per lot). Screw geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production hardware (n=3). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (1000 samples); contribution to total uval < 4%. All inputs traceable to calibrated instruments."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation specimens are production-representative hardware from same manufacturing lot as device under review; N ≥ 5 per laboratory.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production hardware (same manufacturing lot as 510(k) submission device). Six constructs tested at FDA CDRH laboratory, five at DePuy Synthes laboratory. Dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances. Exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; minimum two distinct load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (L5-S1 corpectomy, 35 mm spacer height, 0° lordosis). Only one test condition evaluated; variability in spacer height and lordosis angle not explored. Achieved level 1 falls below required level 2 — identified as a known gap accepted by sponsor based on regulatory precedent for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions, loading) demonstrably equivalent to physical test configuration; any deviations quantified and shown to have negligible effect on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CMM-measured test specimens. Fixture compliance measured and incorporated as spring boundary conditions (k_fixture = 48,000 N/mm). Crosshead displacement applied as prescribed displacement ramp matching test protocol. Equivalency confirmed; residual deviation in boundary stiffness estimated to contribute < 1.5% to QoI uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; relative error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and relative error < 10%. Maximum E/uval = 1.67 (force at 40 mm). Comparison performed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4 using combined experimental and simulation uncertainty. Acceptance criteria met."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission claims and failure modes of concern (construct stiffness, yield, large-displacement load-carrying capacity).",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs cited in the 510(k) predicate comparison and directly address fatigue and fracture risk under spinal loading. QoIs are mechanistically linked to the device failure mode (screw-rod interface loosening and screw fatigue fracture). Relevance confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (ASTM F1717, non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw, production hardware, two independent laboratories) is sufficiently representative of the COU to support the regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on production hardware under the standard regulatory test protocol (ASTM F1717) at two independent laboratories, directly mirroring the COU. The FEA model ensemble spans three independent modeling teams, providing cross-validation of modeling choices. Validation activities judged highly relevant to the COU; achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
