    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted based on regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 single-configuration testing for this device class and is consistent with predicate 510(k) submissions. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%) satisfied for all three primary QoIs across two independent laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission decision.",
